# `std.pwa` — Progressive Web App support

Turns any `.ssc` web app into a PWA in two lines:
register the plugin routes **before** `serve(port)`.

```scalascript
// Register GET /manifest.json and GET /sw.js before serve(port).
//
// Parameters (all optional except name):
//   name            — full app name shown in the OS launcher
//   shortName       — short label (dock, home screen); defaults to name
//   description     — human-readable description
//   themeColor      — toolbar / status-bar colour, e.g. "#4285F4"
//   backgroundColor — splash-screen background, e.g. "#ffffff"
//   display         — "standalone" | "fullscreen" | "minimal-ui" | "browser"
//   startUrl        — URL opened when launched from home screen, default "/"
//   icons           — list of icon URLs (serve them as static files)
//   precache        — URLs cached on service-worker install (cache-first on fetch)
extern def pwa(
  name:            String,
  shortName:       String        = "",
  description:     String        = "",
  themeColor:      String        = "#ffffff",
  backgroundColor: String        = "#ffffff",
  display:         String        = "standalone",
  startUrl:        String        = "/",
  icons:           List[String]  = List(),
  precache:        List[String]  = List()
): Unit
```
